/*
We have the polynom f(x) = 1/3x_1^2 + x_2^2 + x_1 * x_2 + 3

The gradient of f(x):

grad(x) = | x_1^2+x_2 |
          | 2x_2+x_1  |

And thus the Hesse-Matrix H:
| 2x_1  1 |
|  1    2 |

The inverse Hesse-Matrix H^-1 is
| -2 / (1-4x_1)    1 / (1 - 4x_1)     |
| 1 / (1 - 4x_1)   -2x_1 / (1 - 4x_1) |

We now want to find lim ->oo x[n]
column2: with the starting element of (3 2)^T\n\n*/Comment.Multiline
